This week the annual Pan South African Language Board (PanSALB) Multilingualism Awards took place at the Cape Town International Convention Centre. Judge Albie Sachs gave the keynote address, Sports Minister Fikile Mbalula was on hand for the proceedings and a host of South Africans honouring their home languages were there to accept awards and speak out for the rights of their mother tongues. Here&rsquo;s what the awards looked like: